data.title: The Place Where Rutherford B. Hayes Is A Really Big Deal
data.meta_description: The 19th U.S. president didn't leave much of a legacy at home. But in Paraguay, he's a hero, credited with helping save the nation after a disastrous war with its South American neighbors.
